3. Compiling
------------

	3.1 Test GStreamer

		https://gstreamer.freedesktop.org/data/doc/gstreamer/head/faq/html/chapter-using.html
		gst-launch-1.0 filesrc location=~/audiofile.mp3 ! decodebin ! audioconvert ! pulsesink
		gst-launch-1.0 filesrc location=~/videofile.mp4 ! decodebin ! videoconvert ! xvimagesink

		https://gstreamer.freedesktop.org/documentation/tools/gst-launch.html?gi-language=c#pipeline-examples
		./gst-launch-1.0 -v filesrc location=~/audiofile.mp3 ! mpegaudioparse ! avdec_mp3 ! audioconvert ! audioresample ! alsasink

		* Only video
		./gst-launch-1.0 filesrc location=~/videofile.mp4 ! decodebin name=dec ! videoconvert ! autovideosink

		* Video and audio
		./gst-launch-1.0 filesrc location=~/videofile.mp4 ! decodebin name=dec ! videoconvert ! autovideosink dec. ! audioconvert ! audioresample ! alsasink

		* TCP Server
		gst-launch-1.0 -v filesrc location=~/audiofile.mp3 ! mpegaudioparse ! tcpserversink host=0.0.0.0 port=12345
		
		*TCP Client play audio
		gst-launch-1.0 -v tcpclientsrc host=192.168.121.91 port=12345 ! decodebin ! audioconvert ! pulsesink
		

	3.2 Compiling gst-plugin-gmtp

		export PKG_CONFIG_PATH=/home/wendell/gst-bin/lib/pkgconfig
		export LD_LIBRARY_PATH=/home/wendell/gst-bin/lib
		./autogen.sh && ./configure --prefix=/home/wendell/gst-bin && make

		./gst-launch-1.0 -v filesrc location=~/sweetchildomine.mp3 ! mpegaudioparse ! gmtpserversink port=9011
		./gst-launch-1.0 -v gmtpclientsrc host=localhost port=9011 ! decodebin ! audioconvert ! pulsesink

	3.3 Testing gst-plugin-gmtp
		* Serving mp3 file using GMTP Server
		gst-launch-1.0 --gst-plugin-path=$HOME/gmtp/app/gstreamer/gst-plugin-gmtp/src -v filesrc location=~/audiofile.mp3 ! mpegaudioparse ! gmtpserversink port=12345
		
		* Playing remote mp3 file using GMTP client
		gst-launch-1.0 --gst-plugin-path=$HOME/gmtp/app/gstreamer/gst-plugin-gmtp/src -v gmtpclientsrc host=10.10.0.101 port=12345 ! decodebin ! audioconvert ! pulsesink
		
		* Saving (without play) remote mp3 file using GMTP client
                gst-launch-1.0 --gst-plugin-path=$HOME/gmtp/app/gstreamer/gst-plugin-gmtp/src -v gmtpclientsrc host=10.10.0.101 port=12345 ! tee name=tp tp. ! queue ! filesink location=~/audio_copy.mp3 tp. ! queue ! decodebin

	3.4 Pipeline examples
		* Play local mp3 and save it to a new file at the same time
		gst-launch-1.0 -v filesrc location=~/sweetchildomine.mp3 ! tee name=tp tp. ! queue ! filesink location=/tmp/scom2.mp3 tp. ! queue ! decodebin ! audioconvert ! pulsesink
		* Play remote mp3 and save it to a new file at the same time
		gst-launch-1.0 -v gmtpclientsrc host=192.168.25.58 port=12345 ! tee name=tp tp. ! queue ! filesink location=/tmp/scom3.mp3 tp. ! queue ! decodebin ! audioconvert ! pulsesink

4. Porting to GStreamer 1.0
---------------------------

See http://cgit.freedesktop.org/gstreamer/gstreamer/tree/docs/random/porting-to-1.0.txt

HOW TO USE THE TEMPLATE PLUGIN
------------------------------

To use it, either make a copy for yourself and rename the parts or use the
make_element script in tools. To create sources for "myfilter" based on the
"gsttransform" template run:

cd src;
../tools/make_element myfilter gsttransform

This will create gstmyfilter.c and gstmyfilter.h. Open them in an editor and
start editing. There are several occurances of the string "template", update
those with real values. The plugin will be called 'myfilter' and it will have
one element called 'myfilter' too. Also look for "FIXME:" markers that point you
to places where you need to edit the code.

You still need to adjust the Makefile.am.

